name: Rustfang
description: A worn blade with flaking edges. Still good enough to scare off slimebats.

name: Timbertooth
description: Carved from ironwood and nailed with steel teeth. Surprisingly dependable.

name: Ironlink
description: Forged from spare chain loops. It clinks louder than it cuts.

name: Mirepiercer
description: Shaped to jab, not swing. Perfect for stabbing through swamp armor.

name: Glowbrand
description: A simple core blade with a faint internal shimmer. A favorite among trainees.

name: Hollowsteel
description: Thin and light, yet unnaturally strong. Whistles on wide arcs.

name: Splinterblade
description: Jagged like broken glass. You’ll need a steady hand and a lot of gauze.

name: Embercut
description: Warms the air around it. Once used to light torches on expedition trails.

name: Bramblefang
description: Decorated with curling vine patterns. Draws blood like a thorn.

name: Moonbite
description: Faint lunar etchings glow softly in the dark. Feels lighter under starlight.

name: Dusthowl
description: Kicks up air as it swings. Makes more noise than damage — for now.

name: Thorncleave
description: Covered in forged briars. Cuts as it drags. Feared in the undergroves.

name: Starflare
description: Its polished finish reflects starlight in dungeons. Favored by lightseers.

name: Ashsplitter
description: Blackened tip, cool to the touch. Used by fire-walkers of Ember Steppe.

name: Daggerroot
description: The hilt smells faintly of earth. Born from jungle-forged steel.

name: Spiritlash
description: Leaves a faint echo after striking. Those hit feel... slower.

name: Gleamscourge
description: Ornate but deadly. Used in ceremonial duels that rarely ended peacefully.

name: Blightpiercer
description: A twisted core blade once wielded in the Rot Wars. Resists corrosion.

name: Gloomfang
description: The darker it is, the faster it cuts. Whispers when held at dusk.

name: Thunderbite
description: Sparks on metal contact. Loud, erratic, but effective.

name: Barksting
description: Crafted from old wood and thorn. Arrows buzz more than they fly.

name: Sapshot
description: Drips resin from the limbs. Makes quivers stickier than they should be.

name: Driftwhistle
description: Light and wind-tuned. Hums softly when drawn.

name: Mirebranch
description: Found buried in marsh soil. Pulls just a little left with every shot.

name: Glowtwig
description: Dimly radiant under moonlight. A good companion for late hunts.

name: Spindlebend
description: Wobbly-looking but weirdly accurate. Made from scrap and luck.

name: Snarlroot
description: Tensioned too tight, it bites back on misfires. Often wrapped in rags.

name: Hearthbloom
description: Warm to the touch. A popular starter bow for cozy rangers.

name: Vinecoil
description: Flexible frame lashed with living vines. Grows faint leaves over time.

name: Silenttwig
description: Makes no sound. Even the arrows seem surprised when they hit.

name: Flickerbranch
description: Glimmers when turned sideways. Loses shine in direct moonlight.

name: Dustreel
description: Quivers with recoil. Once used in desert duels at dawn.

name: Gleamthread
description: String woven from starlit spider silk. It resets itself overnight.

name: Ashgroove
description: Burnt wood, still glowing faintly. Arrows smell like campfire.

name: Briarhook
description: Fires sticky-tipped arrows that tangle in enemy cloaks.

name: Hushbeam
description: Shots make no noise. Even the wind forgets they passed.

name: Mistfang
description: Tends to fog when drawn. Excellent in ambush-heavy regions.

name: Sporespine
description: Mossy and damp. Arrows grow fluff if left too long.

name: Stonepulse
description: Strikes with heavy force. Arrows hit like falling fruit.

name: Moonbrace
description: Carved beneath lunar eclipse. Favored by owl-eyed archers.

name: Twigwand
description: A snapped stick with ambition. Best for misfires and sparks.

name: Barkroot Rod
description: Smells of wet wood and burnt paper. Casts minor but honest spells.

name: Mossvine Staff
description: Wrapped in creeping green. Useful for growing herbs or headaches.

name: Embertwig
description: Smolders faintly. Will ignite scrolls if held too long.

name: Dewlight Wand
description: Condensation gathers at its tip. Radiates sleepy warmth.

name: Glowsap Channel
description: Translucent wood pulsing with syrupy light. Attracts beetles.

name: Flicker Staff
description: Hard to focus on. Glitches slightly between planes when idle.

name: Thornchant Staff
description: Covered in natural barbs. Enhances curses by at least 12%.

name: Dustcoil Wand
description: Leaves a trail of motes when waved. Best for dramatic exits.

name: Sparkhook
description: Jerks forward on its own when spells are strong.

name: Soulreed
description: Used to stir memory pools. Whispers unintelligibly when near graves.

name: Emberlock
description: Glows red when angry. Locks fire magic into stable orbs.

name: Hollowbloom
description: A staff of dry petals and void. Blossoms only in nightmares.

name: Windcrutch
description: Used to walk on air. Mostly effective on small stairs.

name: Sporespike
description: Rains puffs when slammed. Causes sneezing if used too frequently.

name: Murmuroak
description: The wood murmurs gently. No one knows what it’s saying.

name: Gleamroot
description: Shines through walls. Sometimes inconvenient, always dazzling.

name: Runeberry Rod
description: Dotted with glowing fruit. Casting causes one to vanish.

name: Shardstem
description: Covered in prismatic shards. Shoots rays that taste faintly of ozone.

name: Flowthread Staff
description: Made from silk and sighs. It directs energy like a lazy river.

name: Blight Helm
description: A helm infused with shadowed energy, radiating an aura of corruption and decay.

name: Void Helm
description: A sleek and ethereal helm crafted from voidium, granting enhanced agility and perception.

name: Voidheart Helm
description: A heavy helm forged from concentrated voidium, exuding an unearthly and intimidating presence.

name: Protector Helm
description: A protective helm forged by the ancient Vorloran, symbolizing resilience and vigilance.

name: Watcher Helm
description: This helm sharpens awareness, allowing its wearer to detect unseen threats with ease.

name: Eldritch Hood
description: A hood woven with eldritch threads, crackling with chaotic magic for arcane defense and power.

name: Zephyr Crown
description: A light crown blessed by unseen winds, offering unmatched grace and agility to its wearer.

name: Glacier Crown
description: A crown imbued with eternal frost, protecting the wearer with icy resilience.

name: Terra Crown
description: A sturdy helm rooted in the strength of the earth, granting steadfast protection.

name: Inferno Crown
description: Forged in molten fire, this fiery helm emanates the raw rage of Ragnar’s forge.

name: Blight Plate
description: A corrupted armor forged from shadowed materials, emanating an aura of decay.

name: Void Plate
description: A sleek armor made of voidium, designed for agility and enhanced with ethereal energy.

name: Voidheart Plate
description: A heavy armor forged from condensed voidium, radiating an intimidating and otherworldly presence.

name: Protector Plate
description: Forged by the ancient Vorloran, this plate embodies strength and resilience in battle.

name: Watcher Plate
description: This armor sharpens its wearer’s awareness, aiding in detecting unseen threats.

name: Eldritch Robes
description: Arcane robes crackling with chaotic magic, favored by spellcasters seeking unbridled power.

name: Zephyr Godplate
description: A light and graceful armor, blessed by unseen winds to grant unparalleled mobility in combat.

name: Glacier Godplate
description: Infused with eternal frost, this plate can freeze incoming strikes, making its wearer nearly untouchable.

name: Terra Godplate
description: A sturdy plate forged from the strongest earthly materials, offering unshakable defense in any encounter.

name: Inferno Godplate
description: Born from the molten core of Ragnar’s forge, this armor burns with the rage of a thousand flames.

name: Sticky Shield
description: A basic shield of slimewood, perfect for beginners.

name: Slime Bronze Shield
description: Reinforced with slime-bronze, offering reliable protection.

name: Hardened Shield
description: Made with hardened materials to endure greater impacts.

name: Alloy Shield
description: A balanced shield forged with slime-alloy for versatility.

name: Veil Shield
description: Shadowy and sleek, ideal for silent defenders.

name: Muck Shield
description: Crafted from resilient muckstone, unusually tough.

name: Glow Shield
description: Radiates protective light, instilling courage in its wielder.

name: Frost Shield
description: A frosty shield that chills attackers upon impact.

name: Ember Shield
description: Burns brightly, deflecting attacks with fiery resilience.

name: Relic Shield
description: A relic of old, emanating ancient defensive power.

name: Fracture Shield
description: Forged with dragon’s magma shards, unbreakable and fierce.

name: Gleam Shield
description: Crafted from glittering Crystal, as tough as it is radiant.

name: Verdant Shield
description: Enriched with lush, green Crystal of unparalleled strength.

name: Sanctum Shield
description: A shield of holy power, blessed with sanctified slime.

name: Abyss Shield
description: A dark shield imbued with chaotic abyssal energies.

name: Wisp Shield
description: Flickering with faint light, mysterious and graceful.

name: Dusk Shield
description: Forged in twilight, carrying the essence of dusk.

name: Siphon Shield
description: Draws strength from those it deflects, eerie and powerful.

name: Rift Shield
description: Rips through reality, forged from the Nether’s essence.

name: Eternal Barrier
description: A legendary shield, said to be forged from the core of slimes.

name: Mudmantle
description: A coarse, earth-toned cloak worn by foragers of the rootways. Offers modest defense and maximum blend into bogs and thickets.

name: Verdant Fringe
description: Dyed in mossgreen threads and rimmed in forestleather, this cape hums faintly when the wind stirs. Beloved by glade scouts.

name: Crimson Houndhide
description: Once worn by bloodtrackers during the war of Duskroot. Faint traces of rage remain soaked into its weft.

name: Drakeguard Wrap
description: Gold-threaded and flame-hardened, it bears the heraldry of the Firewatch Order. Useful against both blade and glare.

name: Blazemark Shawl
description: A prestige garb woven for Sun-Chosen tacticians. Radiates faint warmth, even at night.

name: Glaciercoil
description: Cut from frostsilk, its fabric stiffens in cold but never breaks. Trusted by Wind Temple archivists.

name: Emberwing Veil
description: Decorative winged shoulders crafted from emberweave. Bestows fire resistance and flightless flair.

name: Umbravine Mantle
description: Etched with spirals of forgotten glyphs, this deep-violet cloak shimmers with sealed whispers.

name: Ashflame Drape
description: Charred at the edges and stitched with phoenixgold. Said to be reborn anew every full moon.

name: Crownshroud
description: A regal, front-facing cloak set with a soulstone clasp. Crafted for the Slime Regent, said to turn strikes to light.

name: Pendant of Origin
description: Worn by those who walked the world before it was ready. It hums faintly with the echoes of first steps.

name: Luminspire Amulet I
description: A radiant moonstone gem that emanates soft brilliance, gently enhancing the flow of every action.

name: Luminspire Amulet II
description: Refined with celestial energy, this amulet imbues its wearer with unmatched grace and efficiency.

name: Obsidianflare Pendant I
description: A darkly luminous relic that channels the moon’s quiet strength, quickening every effort.

name: Obsidianflare Pendant II
description: Polished to perfection, this artifact transforms work into art, granting seamless motion to all tasks.

name: Amulet of Eternal Lumina
description: The pinnacle of moonstone craftsmanship, this amulet blends light and shadow to create mastery beyond mortal limits.

name: Nightveil Pendant I
description: A glimmering nightopal amulet, cloaked in twilight, it amplifies creation with an enigmatic aura.

name: Nightveil Pendant II
description: Charged with cosmic energy, this pendant magnifies fortune, doubling the bounty of all endeavors.

name: Shadowweave Charm I
description: Forged in secret rites, this pendant draws from hidden depths, ensuring abundance in every outcome.

name: Shadowweave Charm II
description: Etched with forbidden glyphs, this charm turns the ordinary into the extraordinary, multiplying rewards effortlessly.

name: Core of Eternal Darkness
description: A relic of ultimate power, this nightopal core merges shadow and mystery to unlock boundless prosperity for its bearer.
